<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4/dist/leaflet.css"
        integrity="sha256-p4NxAoJBhIIN+hmNHrzRCf9tD/miZyoHS5obTRR9BMY=" crossorigin="" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">

    <title>
        <%= title %>
    </title>

    <meta name="description"
        content="Interactive map of the percentage of people able to speak Irish in each of Ireland's 32 counties, from the 1851 census to 2022.">

    <!-- Open Graph / Twitter, so shared links render a preview card. -->
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Reported ability to speak Irish">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Reported ability to speak Irish, 1851 to 2022">
    <meta property="og:description"
        content="Interactive map of the percentage of people able to speak Irish in each of Ireland's 32 counties, from the 1851 census to 2022.">
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://acoci86.github.io/irish-language-map/">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://acoci86.github.io/irish-language-map/screenshot.png">
    <meta property="og:image:width" content="1920">
    <meta property="og:image:height" content="995">
    <meta property="og:image:alt"
        content="Map of Ireland shaded by the percentage of people able to speak Irish in each county.">
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
</head>

<body>
    <header>
        <h1>
            Reported ability to speak Irish
        </h1>

        <p class="lead">
            Percentage of people aged 3 and over who reported that they could
            speak Irish. This measures self-reported ability, not fluency or
            regular use.
        </p>

        <div class="controls">
            <button id="play-button" type="button" aria-pressed="false">
                <svg class="btn-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"/></svg>
                Play
            </button>

            <label for="year-select">Census year</label>
            <select id="year-select">
              <% abilityYears.forEach((year) => { %>
                <option
                  value="<%= year %>"
                  <%= year === defaultYear ? "selected" : "" %>
                >
                  <%= year %>
                </option>
              <% }); %>
            </select>
        </div>

    </header>

    <main>
        <div class="board">
            <div class="map-box">
                <div id="map"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="side">
                <div id="legend" class="map-legend"></div>

                <aside id="county-panel" class="county-panel" hidden>
                    <button id="county-panel-close" class="county-panel-close" type="button" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
                    <div id="county-panel-body"></div>
                </aside>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p class="data-source">
            Data:
            <a href="https://data.cso.ie/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CSO</a>
            and the Northern Ireland censuses, the latter compiled by
            <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/phelimbirch.bsky.social" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Phelim Birch</a>.
            Boundaries: OSi and OSNI.
        </p>

        <details class="data-notes">
            <summary>About this data</summary>

            <p>
                Census questions and definitions changed over time, so
                comparisons between distant years should be interpreted
                cautiously. The CSO notes that results such as 1926 and 2022
                are not directly comparable, and a new question series began
                in 1996.
            </p>

            <p>
                Northern Ireland recorded Irish only in the all-island
                censuses of 1851 to 1911 and again from 1991, so the six
                counties show as "no data" in between. Its 2001 and 2021
                censuses appear under 2002 and 2022; the county card says so
                when that applies. Antrim and Down for 1851, 1861 and 1901 are
                estimated, because Belfast straddles both counties.
            </p>

            <p>
                Some Northern Ireland county figures are themselves estimates.
                The 1991, 2001 and 2011 values were derived from ward-level
                returns, and NISRA's 2021 county figures are estimated from
                census areas, as the North does not publish this on a county
                basis directly.
            </p>
        </details>

        <a
            class="github-link"
            href="https://github.com/ACoci86/irish-language-map"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
        >
            <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"></path>
            </svg>
            View the code on GitHub
        </a>
    </footer>

</body>

<script src="https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4/dist/leaflet.js"
    integrity="sha256-20nQCchB9co0qIjJZRGuk2/Z9VM+kNiyxNV1lvTlZBo=" crossorigin="">

    </script>

<script src="js/map.js"></script>

</html>